This creates a very basic visual representation of an Instagram feed using HTML for structure and CSS for styling. It focuses on the layout of a header, posts, and a footer, without any JavaScript functionality.

### Step-by-step approach

1.  **Create `index.html`**: This file will contain the structure of our webpage, including the header, main content (posts), and footer.
2.  **Create `style.css`**: This file will contain all the CSS rules to style our HTML elements, making them look like a simple Instagram interface.
3.  **Link CSS to HTML**: In `index.html`, link `style.css` within the `<head>` section.
4.  **Build Header**: Add a simple header with a title inside `index.html`.
5.  **Build Main Content (Posts)**: Create a container for posts, and then individual `post` divs, each containing a placeholder image and a caption/description.
6.  **Build Footer**: Add a simple footer with copyright information.
7.  **Apply Basic Styles**: Use CSS to reset default browser styles, center content, and define basic font styles.
8.  **Style Header**: Style the header to be fixed at the top, with a background color and padding.
9.  **Style Posts**: Style the individual post containers, images, and captions for a clean, card-like appearance.
10. **Style Footer**: Style the footer to be at the bottom of the page.

### Code

**`index.html`**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SimpleInstaClone</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Grand+Hotel&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="navbar">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="logo">InstaClone</h1>
            <!-- In a real app, you'd have nav links, search, user icon here -->
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="feed container">
        <div class="post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/30/ccc/white?text=A" alt="Profile pic" class="profile-pic">
                <span class="username">UserOne</span>
            </div>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x600?text=Post+Image+1" alt="Post 1" class="post-image">
            <div class="post-footer">
                <div class="actions">
                    <!-- Icons for like, comment, share -->
                    <span>❤️</span> <span>💬</span> <span>✈️</span>
                </div>
                <p class="likes">1,234 likes</p>
                <p class="caption"><span class="username">UserOne</span> This is my first awesome post! #instaclone #webdev</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/30/ccc/white?text=B" alt="Profile pic" class="profile-pic">
                <span class="username">AnotherUser</span>
            </div>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x600?text=Post+Image+2" alt="Post 2" class="post-image">
            <div class="post-footer">
                <div class="actions">
                    <span>❤️</span> <span>💬</span> <span>✈️</span>
                </div>
                <p class="likes">567 likes</p>
                <p class="caption"><span class="username">AnotherUser</span> Enjoying the simple life. #minimalist #coding</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Add more posts as needed -->

    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2023 InstaClone. Not a real Instagram.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

